parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: I didn’t know what was happening to me.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: My tummy hurt, I felt my tummy

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: but I couldn’t get any words out.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: Am I in prison? Am I in hospital?’

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and I wanted to throw up

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and a nurse came and said, ‘What’s wrong with you?

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: Don’t make a mess in that bed’.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and every now and then they came and held our faces

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and said ‘‘shut up, just shut up!’.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: women crying here and women crying there,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: I had already realised that they’d been sterilised,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: A bit later the doctor came

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: He didn’t ask what was wrong with us,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: he just gave us the injection and said

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: ‘you’re discharged and you have to go home.’

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: So I went out of the hospital with my tummy,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: all of the women went out, not just me, all of us holding onto our tummies.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: There was no transport arranged for us,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: we all had to make our own way home..
